the comparative perspective leads us to discover surprising similarities. Disparate encounters are connected by their transnational or national perspectives, with the one side criticizing in the interest of rationality as a model of authorization, and the other presenting revelation as a critique of a depraved form of rationality. The thoughtful essays presented herein, by Simon Gerber, Johannes Zachhuber, Jonathan Garb, Rivka Feldhay, Paul Mendes-Flohr, Israel Gershoni and Christoph Schmidt, provide a counterweight to the popularity of some all-too-simplified models of modernization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022)  aEnlightenment, Kabbalah, philosophy, Modern times.1 aFeldhay, Rivka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedmann, Yohanan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGarb, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerber, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGershoni, Israel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarkschies, Christoph , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMarkschies, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMendes-Flohr, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmidt, Christoph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZachhuber, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBoo